Great catch! ğŸ”  
You're absolutely right â€” in the **default Blazor Server template for .NET 6**, you'll usually see this setup:

- âœ… `_Host.cshtml` defines the Blazor server rendering pipeline â€” it injects the layout.
- âœ… `Pages/_Layout.cshtml` contains the actual `<html>`, `<head>`, and `<body>` tags.

---

### âœ… So: Where to put your script tags?

ğŸ‘‰ **Place the following script tags inside `_Layout.cshtml`**, **right before the closing `</body>` tag**:

```html
<script src="js/plotly/dist/plotly.min.js"></script>
<script src="js/plotlyInterop.js"></script>
<script src="_framework/blazor.server.js"></script>
```

ğŸ“Œ Why this order?
- `plotly.min.js` â†’ loads Plotly core
- `plotlyInterop.js` â†’ defines `renderPlotlyBarChart()`
- `blazor.server.js` â†’ Blazor framework starts last

---

### âš ï¸ Important
If you accidentally put your Plotly JS **after** `blazor.server.js`, youâ€™ll get the `renderPlotlyBarChart is undefined` error â€” like earlier.

